#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.28:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.28:0.2"
msgid "3. Micchattavagga"
msgstr "3. The Wrong Way"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn45.28:0.3"
msgid "28. Samādhisutta"
msgstr "28. Immersion"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.28:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

# Compare AN 7.45.
msgctxt "sn45.28:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Ariyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, sammāsamādhiṃ desessāmi saupanisaṃ saparikkhāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you noble right immersion with its vital "
"conditions and its prerequisites."

msgctxt "sn45.28:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn45.28:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, ariyo sammāsamādhi saupaniso saparikkhāro?"
msgstr ""
"And what is noble right immersion with its vital conditions and its "
"prerequisites?"

#. VAR: sammāsati → sammāsamādhi (si, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn45.28:1.5"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsati."
msgstr ""
"There are right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right "
"livelihood, right effort, and right mindfulness."

#. VAR: saparikkhāratā → saparikkhatā (si, s1-3) | saparikkhārā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn45.28:1.6"
msgid "Yā kho, bhikkhave, imehi sattahaṅgehi cittassa ekaggatā saparikkhāratā—"
msgstr ""
"Unification of mind with these seven factors as prerequisites is called "
"noble right immersion ‘with its vital conditions’ and ‘with its "
"prerequisites’.”"

msgctxt "sn45.28:1.7"
msgid ""
"ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyo sammāsamādhi saupaniso itipi saparikkhāro "
"itipī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.28:1.8"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
